        <num>CC 1887</num>
        <heading>1887.  Discharge of any prior obligor does not affect security</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1887.  Discharge of any prior obligor does not affect security
If the new obligor has assumed the obligation and acquired the thing given as security, the discharge of any prior obligor by the obligee does not affect the security or its rank.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=109131</p>
        </authorialNote>
